{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52880535-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s605"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"605"},"text":"§ 605.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Budget estimates","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Director, under the supervision of the Judicial Conference of the United States, shall submit to the Office of Management and Budget annual estimates of the expenditures and appropriations necessary for the maintenance and operation of the courts and the Administrative Office and the operation of the judicial survivors annuity fund, and such supplemental and deficiency estimates as may be required from time to time for the same purposes, according to law. The Director shall cause periodic examinations of the judicial survivors annuity fund to be made by an actuary, who may be an actuary employed by another department of the Government temporarily assigned for the purpose, and whose findings and recommendations shall be transmitted by the Director to the Judicial Conference.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Such estimates shall be approved, before presentation to the Office of Management and Budget, by the Judicial Conference of the United States, except that the estimate with respect to the Court of International Trade shall be approved by such court and the estimate with respect to the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit shall be approved by such court.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52880536-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/915"},"text":"62 Stat. 915","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-07-09/ch517/s1/e"},"text":"July 9, 1956, ch. 517, § 1(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70/497"},"text":"70 Stat. 497","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-03/ch944/s4"},"text":"Aug. 3, 1956, ch. 944, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70/1026"},"text":"70 Stat. 1026","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/253/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–253, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-09-19"},"text":"Sept. 19, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/521"},"text":"75 Stat. 521","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417/tV/s501/14"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417, title V, § 501(14)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1742"},"text":"94 Stat. 1742","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164/tI/s119/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164, title I, § 119(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-04-02"},"text":"Apr. 2, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/33"},"text":"96 Stat. 33","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258/s5/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258, § 5(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1068"},"text":"96 Stat. 1068","children":[],"tail":", 1085.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52880537-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52880538-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 447 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s305"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 305","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-08-07/ch501/s1"},"text":"Aug. 7, 1939, ch. 501, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/1223"},"text":"53 Stat. 1223","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section contains provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s447"},"text":"section 447 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., relating to budget estimates. The remainder of said section 447 is incorporated in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s604"},"text":"section 604 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The designation “senior circuit judges” was changed to “chief judges of the circuits” in conformity with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s45"},"text":"section 45 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes were made in phraseology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id52880539-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Senate Revision Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Those provisions of this section which related to the Tax Court were eliminated by Senate amendment. See 80th Congress Senate Report No. 1559.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id5288053a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id5288053b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258","children":[],"tail":" struck out paragraph which had provided that budget estimates be included in the budget without revision, but subject to the recommendations of the Bureau of the Budget, as provided by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s11"},"text":"section 11 of Title 31","children":[],"tail":" for the estimates of the Supreme Court. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1105/b"},"text":"section 1105(b) of Title 31","children":[],"tail":", Money and Finance."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Office of Management and Budget” for “Bureau of the Budget” wherever appearing and inserted requirement that the estimate of the expenditures and appropriations necessary for the maintenance and operation of the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit be approved by such court."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417","children":[],"tail":" redesignated the Customs Court as the Court of International Trade."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1961—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/253"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–253","children":[],"tail":" struck out from second paragraph the requirement that the estimate with respect to the Court of Customs and Patent Appeals be approved by such court."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1956—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-08-03"},"text":"Aug. 3, 1956","children":[],"tail":", inserted provision to authorize the Director to include in the budget estimates of the courts the expenditures and appropriations necessary for the operation of the judicial survivors annuity fund, and inserted provision that Director shall cause periodic actuarial examinations to be made of the judicial survivors annuity fund and shall report the actuary’s findings and recommendations to the Judicial Conference."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-07-09"},"text":"July 9, 1956","children":[],"tail":", struck out “and the Court of Claims” after “the Customs Court” and substituted “and” for the comma after “the Court of Customs and Patents Appeals” in second par."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id5288053c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id5288053d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1982 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1982","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164/s402"},"text":"section 402 of Pub. L. 97–164","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s171"},"text":"section 171 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id5288053e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1980","children":[],"tail":", and applicable with respect to civil actions pending on or commenced on or after such date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417/s701/a"},"text":"section 701(a) of Pub. L. 96–417","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s251"},"text":"section 251 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
